Systems Reqs menu level 1 item 1 of 7Security menu level 1 item 2 of 7Privacy menu level 1 item 3 of 7Bus. Continuity Plan menu level 1 item 4 of 7Contact Us menu level 1 item 5 of 7Broker Check Notification menu level 1 item 6 of 7Website Terms & Conditions menu level 1 item 7 of 7
Sub-Account(s) refer to the underlying investment options in the variable annuity.
Great-West Smart Track® variable annuities are sold by prospectus only. The investment return and principal value of a variable annuity will fluctuate so that an investor's units, when redeemed, may be more or less than their original cost. Before purchasing an annuity, you should carefully consider its investment options' objectives, and all the risks, charges and expenses associated with the annuity and its investment options. For this and other important information please call 1-877-723-8723 to request an annuity prospectus for Great-West Smart Track or Great-West Smart Track II, or you can view the prospectus for the annuities or their underlying funds, online. Please read them carefully before investing or sending money.

Variable annuities are suitable for long-term goals, such as retirement; and, under current federal tax law, any withdrawals of earnings prior to age 59½  may be subject to income tax and a 10% penalty.

The  principal underwriter for the Great-West Smart Track® variable  annuities is GWFS Equities, Inc., and securities, when offered, are offered through  GWFS Equities, Inc. and/or other broker dealers. 

